Others: Pakistan batter Saud Shakeel said that he developed his game according to the team's needs after scoring a half-century against Netherlands in the ongoing ICC Men's Cricket World Cup 2023.
Shakeel scored 68 runs off 52 balls, smashing nine boundaries and a solitary six.
Shakeel walked in when Pakistan were reeling at 38 for 3, with Fakhar Zaman, skipper Babar Azam and Imam-ul-Haq back in the pavilion.
Shakeel was positive from the get-go and formed a crucial 120-run partnership with wicket-keeping batter Mohammad Rizwan.
The two batters lifted Pakistan from a dangerous position to a comfortable one in the space of 20 overs.
